05/01/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The Interior Ministry announced on Thursday (January 4th) that Serbia would begin issuing new biometric passports before the end of January.
The new ones would contain data such as face analysis, fingerprints, signature, digital picture and digital fingerprints, in part to help fight organised crime and terrorism.
The ministry says that by July 2011, all Serbian citizens above the age of 16 should have biometric passports.
(RTS - 04/01/07)
